<p>The <b>democratization of knowledge</b> is the acquisition and spread of <a href="/wiki/Knowledge" title="Knowledge">knowledge</a> amongst the common people, not just privileged <a href="/wiki/Elite" title="Elite">elites</a> such as clergy and academics. Libraries—public libraries in particular—and modern digital technology such as the internet—play a key role in the democratization of knowledge, as they provide open access of information to the masses.</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
